#MEM id=systematic-debugging source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/quinn/skills/superpowers/systematic-debugging/defense-in-depth.md
M|systematic-debugging|When you fix a bug caused by invalid data, adding validation at one place feels sufficient. But that single check can be bypassed by different code paths, refactoring, or mocks.
M|systematic-debugging|**Core principle:** Validate at EVERY layer data passes through. Make the bug structurally impossible.
M|systematic-debugging|Single validation: "We fixed the bug"
M|systematic-debugging|Multiple layers: "We made the bug impossible"
M|systematic-debugging|Different layers catch different cases:
M|systematic-debugging|- Entry validation catches most bugs
M|systematic-debugging|- Business logic catches edge cases
M|systematic-debugging|- Environment guards prevent ctx-specific dangers
M|systematic-debugging|- Debug logging helps when other layers fail
M|systematic-debugging|**Purpose:** Reject obviously invalid input at API boundary
M|systematic-debugging|```typescript
M|systematic-debugging|function createProject(name: string, workingDirectory: string) {
M|systematic-debugging|if (!workingDirectory || workingDirectory.trim() === '') {
M|systematic-debugging|throw new Error('workingDirectory cannot be empty');
M|systematic-debugging|}
M|systematic-debugging|if (!existsSync(workingDirectory)) {
M|systematic-debugging|throw new Error(`workingDirectory does not exist: ${workingDirectory}`);
M|systematic-debugging|}
M|systematic-debugging|if (!statSync(workingDirectory).isDirectory()) {
M|systematic-debugging|throw new Error(`workingDirectory is not a directory: ${workingDirectory}`);
M|systematic-debugging|}
M|systematic-debugging|// ... proceed
M|systematic-debugging|}
M|systematic-debugging|```
M|systematic-debugging|**Purpose:** Ensure data makes sense for this operation
