M|systematic-debugging|When you find a bug:
M|systematic-debugging|1. **Trace the data flow** - Where does bad value originate? Where used?
M|systematic-debugging|2. **Map all checkpoints** - List every point data passes through
M|systematic-debugging|3. **Add validation at each layer** - Entry, business, environment, debug
M|systematic-debugging|4. **Test each layer** - Try to bypass layer 1, verify layer 2 catches it
M|systematic-debugging|Bug: Empty `projectDir` caused `git init` in source code
M|systematic-debugging|**Data flow:**
M|systematic-debugging|1. Test setup → empty string
M|systematic-debugging|2. `Project.create(name, '')`
M|systematic-debugging|3. `WorkspaceManager.createWorkspace('')`
M|systematic-debugging|4. `git init` runs in `process.cwd()`
M|systematic-debugging|**Four layers added:**
M|systematic-debugging|- Layer 1: `Project.create()` validates not empty/exists/writable
M|systematic-debugging|- Layer 2: `WorkspaceManager` validates projectDir not empty
M|systematic-debugging|- Layer 3: `WorktreeManager` refuses git init outside tmpdir in tests
M|systematic-debugging|- Layer 4: Stack trace logging before git init
M|systematic-debugging|**Result:** All 1847 tests passed, bug impossible to reproduce
M|systematic-debugging|All four layers were necessary. During testing, each layer caught bugs the others missed:
M|systematic-debugging|- Different code paths bypassed entry validation
M|systematic-debugging|- Mocks bypassed business logic checks
M|systematic-debugging|- Edge cases on different platforms needed environment guards
M|systematic-debugging|- Debug logging identified structural misuse
M|systematic-debugging|**Don't stop at one validation point.** Add checks at every layer.